This is my VERY first map I ever created. It is a Zombie map. I would not really recomend it for anything else.
Since this is a zombie map,  (and my first map) it does not have a custom made nav file, so the bots can be a bit stupid sometimes.

The zombies cannot leave spawn area, you must make your way to them & open the door that lets the zombies out.

ABOUT THE MAP:
the map itself is a series of zombie maps to come. Basicly, the maps are different parts of a giant facility, this part will be the office part of the facility, where the people who have no idea whats going on below work.
The other parts will be a recycling facility, Labs, Chemical storage, and power.

I will also modify the maps to be playable in Hl2 single player mode.
these will be the map names:

Infiltration (lvl1)
Greenhouse (lvl2)
Nightmare (lvl3)
Under the Rug (lvl4)
Night light (lvl5)
Escape (lvl1 modifyed)

The best part of this map that I think is the secret. 

the secret is a safe room where no zombie can possibly get to you. (or unfortunatly you get to him) I call it the "Chill room"

Story A large bridge in Europe has been hit by a strange object that first seemed to be a meteor. But it came out that this rock was filled with an unknown organic and even moving liquid, which turns humans into zombies by slipping through the ears inside their brains. You, member of a special group, should clear out the hostile liquid and infected humans to banish all risks. (Unluckily, as we already now, one member of the group became alien and then infected the others who are trying to save themselves now...) FPS I got about 60 FPS everywhere, sometimes even 110, although my comp is quite old.. so it wont lag while playing online. ZM_ECHO_WAREHOUSE_BETA
Created By: £cho

Last Updated: April 20, 2008
Maximum Spawn Points: 64
Recommend Player Count: 24-32
Average FPS (for me locally): 200-300FPS

A recently abandoned warehouse has been suspiciously quiet after recent reports of undead activity. With little communication, the first SWAT units to arrive on scene were never to be seen again, and you are dispatched with a second battalion to find the missing units and rid of the zombies once and for all.

Not the best plot, I know, but the map is actually quite detailed. I used a new lighting technique I've been absolutely dying to try out, and I think it came out really nice. The interiors of both buildings are covered in decals and barricading areas, while the outside receives the nighttime lighting and plenty of areas to climb. This is a beta version, and there's no 3D skybox as I didn't get around to making one yet, but you can be sure that it will be included in the next release, so please try not to complain too much again that.

As always, feel free to express your own opinion about the map!
I'd love to hear what players have to say. ^_^
It's been a while since I've gotten around to releasing a map on FPSB. =D

Thanks and enjoy!

Regards,
£cho

ZM_ECHO_RIOT! ============ I figured it's been a while since I've mapped for ZM, so I whipped this map together in about 18-20 hours or so. Don't let the time I spent on this map fool you though, as I worked very hard on this one. There's two main areas to the map. First, there's an aboveground area with a radio tower of sorts in the middle of a storage yard. This area involves a lot of climbing and some barricading. Additionally, there's an underground office-type area filled with barricadeable rooms. This way both parties are pleased, and there's plenty of places to support up to 32 players, though 24 is probably ideal. Before anyone asks, I created this from scratch with little to no reference material. That being said, I think both areas look pretty realistic and came out quite well. And yes, there is at least one secret to be found. ^_^ Oh, and before I forget, check out my gaming community @ www.ke0.us! We have this map running on our ZombieMod server if you'd ever like to test it out. If anyone ever feels like making a remake of this map, that's fine, but please contact me before you release it and be sure to include my name in the credits as the original creator of the map as I have here. So yeah, thanks for downloading and enjoy the map! =D
